cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper involves the use of a mobile robot to aid in energy balancing in the WSN, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of multiple-link mobility diversity algorithm to mitigate the effect of small-scale fading at various wireless links, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper involves the use of multiple agents (sensor nodes, cluster heads, mobile robot) to achieve a common goal, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the use of a control algorithm (multiple-link mobility diversity algorithm) to optimize the performance of the WSN, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
